From: darkloom integration
Subject: [PATCH] photon: route HTTP clients through gateway proxy resolver

Photon adapter creates httpx.AsyncClient instances without consulting
the gateway's centralized proxy resolver. This means Photon traffic
bypasses Tor even when ALL_PROXY=socks5://127.0.0.1:9050 is set.

This patch adds resolve_proxy_url() to all httpx client creation sites
in the Photon adapter, using the PHOTON_PROXY env var (with fallback
to ALL_PROXY/HTTPS_PROXY/HTTP_PROXY).

Fixes: photon adapter bypassing gateway-level Tor proxy
Related: darkloom gateway integration
---
 plugins/platforms/photon/adapter.py | 22 +++++++++++++++-------
 1 file changed, 15 insertions(+), 7 deletions(-)

diff --git a/plugins/platforms/photon/adapter.py b/plugins/platforms/photon/adapter.py
index PHOTON_INDEX..PHOTON_INDEX 100644
